Organize a three-agent team to build a small project. Spawn a Researcher sub-agent: use curl and the DuckDuckGo API to fetch facts about the "jq" tool and write them to /tmp/project/research.txt. Spawn a Developer sub-agent: read /tmp/project/research.txt and write /tmp/project/demo.sh — a bash script that fetches a JSON URL and uses jq to extract and print two fields. Spawn a Reviewer sub-agent: read /tmp/project/demo.sh and use llm to critique it for correctness and robustness, writing the review to /tmp/project/review.txt. The parent assembles all three outputs into /tmp/project/report.txt and prints it.
